geneVariantDescriptions.description: KRAS G12C is a hotspot mutation that lies within a GTP-binding region of the Kras protein (UniProt.org). G12C results in decreased Kras GTPase activity and activation of downstream signaling in cell culture and mouse models (PMID: 26037647 PMID: 16051643, PMID: 23455880).
